    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to observe water-line emission from two low-mass protostars, HOPS 87 (=OMC3-MMS6) and NGC 1333 IRAS4B. Thereby we will search for the kinematic signature of their envelope-disk accretion flows. We will also characterize, via water-line and continuum emission, their underlying disks and the shocks driven by their outflows. In so doing we will test two alternative proposals for the origin of the bright mid-and far-infrared water emission observed in these objects: whether dominantly from the envelope-disk shock or from the outflow. This program has the potential to make the first clear identification of emission from envelope-disk accretion flows, which would provide an important new observational window into the formation of protoplanetary disks.</prp:abstract>
